(29, 1, '2016-10-11 14:49:47', '2016-10-11 14:49:47', 'Establishment of People’s Sustainable Platform for Poverty Reduction (EPSPPR) project is an Information and Communication Technology (ICT) center based project of Caritas Bangladesh (CB) started from April 2014 with the financial support from Caritas Switzerland (CACH) for three years. It is the first initiative of CB to provide ICT center based services including free information services to rural people for taking different opportunities/advantages of ICT services for improvement of their socio-economic condition, livelihood, Government/non-Government services/facilities for reducing poverty, and making aware of their different rights. The project has seven ICT centers; two in Sirajdikhan <em>upazila</em> under Munshigan district, one in Nawabgonj <em>upazila</em> under Dhaka district, three in Modhupur <em>upazila</em> under Tangail district and one in Fulbaria <em>upazila</em> under Mymensingh district. Seven ICT centers are providing different services to the local people of more than 35 villages. The project activities are in implementation under Caritas Dhaka and Mymensingh Regions. For the participation, involvement, support and developing ownership of local community people, each ICT center has one Alliance/Forum, one Managing Committee (MC) and one Youth Club (YC). Total 23 staff of CB are implementing the project activities and running seven ICT centers jointly with local community people.', 'Project Summary', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'project-summary', '', '', '2016-10-13 00:39:53', '2016-10-13 00:39:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost/epsppr_project/?p=29', 0, 'post', '', 0),
